Over 18,000 Private Enterprises Operate in Myanmar 
Private business enterprises, registered with the Myanmar Ministry for
Operation, totaled 18,769 by the end of January this year, according to
the latest figures published by the ministry.
The enterprises, which are running in various forms, include 8,521
Myanmar companies, 7,143 exporters and importers, 1,940 business
representatives, 1,162 partnership firms and 3 chambers of commerce.
Active and increased participation of private sector especially in the
areas of trade and investment has played a leading role in Myanmar
since it moved towards market-oriented economy in late 1988.
According to the official statistics, the contribution of private
sector to the GDP and export were 76.4 percent and 50.2 percent
respectively.
